items.name: Full-Adder-Using-Half-Adder
items.description: A Full Adder is a combinational logic circuit that adds three binary digits: two significant bits and a carry-in (C_in). It produces a sum (S) and a carry-out (C_out). The Full Adder can be implemented using two Half Adders and an OR gate.
